bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The George Washington Alumni Association (GWAA) was founded to strengthen the relationship between alumni and the University. There are alumni programs for each school at the university as well as associated alumni groups such as Columbian Women and the Society of the Emeriti. Alumni affairs reports to the Vice President for Academic Affairs.
This history note was written in 2005.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in the collection includes photographs and negatives of President Trachtenberg, events, alumni reunion weekends, campus buildings, Distinguished Alumni Awards dinners, homecomings, alumni on the cover of Time, and Alumni Achievement Awards.

The collection also includes print materials regarding annual meetings, addresses, events calendars, publications, questionnaires, reunions, Honorary Degrees, special events, Alumni Directories, the General Alumni Association, meeting minutes, Cherry Tree and National University Law School yearbooks, and plaques. Materials in the collection range in date from 1848-2010. Note: Not all series are processed. Ask staff for assistance.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into 23 series: Photographs; Memorabilia; Alumni house files; Photographs of distinguished alumni; General alumni association files; Alumni association board of directors files; T-shirt; Binders; Contact sheets and negatives; Photos from old events; Historic materials; Images of distinguished alumni; Photos of President Trachtenberg; Alumni directories; General alumni association files; Yearbooks and memorabilia; Alumni association files; Alumni weekend; Notebook; Alumni files; Law alumni photographs; GW Impact, report on philanthropy; and a file on alumni killed in the September 11 attacks. There is no series 19.
